<h2>Known problems</h2>
<ul>
	<li>Current glibcs only work on kernel which have a working
	sysmips implementation. There is currently NO kernel with a correct
	implementation. There is at least a workaround to not let the
	binaries issueing an sysmips/_test_and_set to catch an illegal instruction
	exception</li>

	<li>No boot floppies for mips and mipsel</li>

	<li>Current cvs has a broken ext2 - bitops.h should be broken</li>
</ul>

